Global Aircraft Aerostructures Market Insights
Aircraft Aerostructures Market size was valued at USD 70 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 90 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 4.0% from 2024 to 2030.

Aircraft Aerostructures Market Overview
The global aircraft aerostructures market was valued at approximately USD 80 billion in 2024 and is projected to reach USD 120 billion by 2030, expanding at a CAGR of 7.2% from 2024 to 2030. The market is driven by the increasing demand for commercial and military aircraft, rising air travel, and technological advancements in materials and manufacturing processes. The aerospace industry’s shift toward lightweight, fuel-efficient, and high-performance materials has significantly bolstered the aerostructures segment. Growth is further fueled by the expanding production rates of aircraft, including narrow-body and wide-body planes, and the need for replacements and upgrades in older fleets.

